<paragraph id="8B9898347E6EFFE2FF3F76BFDD12F92E" blockId="28.[192,1440,1429,1749]" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="B95344267E6EFFE2FF3F76BFDE4CFA56" bold="true" box="[192,338,1429,1453]" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">Definition.</emphasis>
A possible sister to 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E6EFFE2FDBC76BFDC28FA55" authority="Mabille, 1898" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1898" box="[579,822,1429,1454]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Falga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E6EFFE2FDBC76BFDD94FA56" box="[579,650,1429,1453]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">Falga</emphasis>
Mabille, 1898
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="549C26967E6EFFE2FCBA76BCDC65FA55" box="[837,891,1430,1454]" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E6EFFE2FC2276BFDA5BFA55" authority="Butler, 1870" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1870" box="[989,1349,1429,1454]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Carystus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jeconia">
<emphasis id="B95344267E6EFFE2FC2276BFDBBBFA56" box="[989,1189,1429,1453]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">Carystus jeconia</emphasis>
Butler, 1870
</taxonomicName>
) and in a different subtribe from 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E6EFFE2FE0C769DDC02FA35" authority="Godman, [1900]" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" box="[499,796,1462,1486]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Vacerra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E6EFFE2FE0C769DDD4DFA35" box="[499,595,1463,1486]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">Vacerra</emphasis>
Godman, [1900]
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="549C26967E6EFFE2FCD3769CDC7CFA35" box="[812,866,1462,1486]" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E6EFFE2FC3A769DDA46FA35" authority="Hewitson, [1866]" authorityName="Hewitson" authorityYear="1866" box="[965,1368,1462,1486]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hesperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="litana">
<emphasis id="B95344267E6EFFE2FC3A769DDB9CFA35" box="[965,1154,1462,1486]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">Hesperia litana</emphasis>
Hewitson, [1866]
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation id="131C84B17E6EFFE2FA8F769CDFFEFA14" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="25.[192,275,1594,1616]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,215,1561]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[192,1440,213,1561]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Figure 10. Genomic trees of Erionotini, Carystina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677255" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677255/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Keys to M.23.9. in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6E5C57E6EFFE2FE2F76F2DD6CFA14" author="Evans" box="[464,626,1495,1519]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="28" pageNumber="27" pagination="54 - 88" refId="ref27591" refString="Evans, W. H. 1955. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part IV. Hesperiinae and Megathyminae. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 499 p., pl. 54 - 88" type="book chapter" year="1955">Evans (1955)</bibRefCitation>
. Diagnosed by large and broad square palpi that are longer than the head, 2nd segment longer than usual and directed forward rather than dorsad, and 3rd segment very small; hindwing with a middle straight cream band on both sides. Genitalia illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6E5C57E6EFFE2FAE37533DA85F9CA" author="Bell" box="[1308,1435,1561,1585]" firstAuthor="Bell" pageId="28" pageNumber="27" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref26731" refString="Bell, E. L. 1959. Descriptions of some new species of neotropical Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera, Rhopalocera). American Museum Novitates 1962: 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1959">Bell (1959</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 18): uncus shorter than tegumen, arms rounded, gnathos longer than tegumen, saccus is very short, almost vestigial, valva broadens caudad, harpe short, upturned, joint with ampulla, without teeth or processes (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6E5C57E6EFFE2FEC07551DEADF968" author="Bell" box="[319,435,1659,1683]" firstAuthor="Bell" pageId="28" pageNumber="27" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref26731" refString="Bell, E. L. 1959. Descriptions of some new species of neotropical Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera, Rhopalocera). American Museum Novitates 1962: 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1959">Bell 1959</bibRefCitation>
). In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly1603.20.1:G64A, aly84.28.1:C2633G, aly707.2.13:T749A, aly798.5.3:G284G (not A), aly291.21.2:T2561T (not G), aly102.6.2:G1936G (not A).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33DCBBF7E6EFFE2FF3F75C4DC9BF873" pageId="28" pageNumber="27" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B9898347E6EFFE2FF3F75C4DBDFF8DD" blockId="28.[192,1440,1774,1831]" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="B95344267E6EFFE2FF3F75C4DE45F8FD" bold="true" box="[192,347,1774,1798]" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is a feminine noun in the nominative singular, formed as a fusion of the species names: senior and junior synonyms referring to the 
<typeStatus id="549C26967E6EFFE2FCC37425DC66F8DC" box="[828,888,1807,1831]" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">Type</typeStatus>
species. 
<emphasis id="B95344267E6EFFE2FC1A7425DB0DF8DD" box="[997,1043,1807,1830]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">Bar</emphasis>
[roni + m] 
<emphasis id="B95344267E6EFFE2FB737424DBA4F8DD" box="[1164,1210,1806,1830]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">olla</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9898347E6EFFE2FF3F7415DDDDF8A3" blockId="28.[192,707,1855,1880]" box="[192,707,1855,1880]" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="B95344267E6EFFE2FF3F7415DEAEF8AC" bold="true" box="[192,432,1855,1879]" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">Species included.</emphasis>
Only the 
<typeStatus id="549C26967E6EFFE2FDD6746ADD40F8A3" box="[553,606,1856,1880]" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">type</typeStatus>
species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9898347E6EFFE2FF3F745ADC9BF873" blockId="28.[192,901,1904,1928]" box="[192,901,1904,1928]" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="B95344267E6EFFE2FF3F745ADE62F873" bold="true" box="[192,380,1904,1928]" pageId="28" pageNumber="27">Parent taxon.</emphasis>
Subtribe 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E6EFFE2FE0A745ADD4DF873" authorityName="Grishin" authorityYear="2019" box="[501,595,1904,1928]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Falgina">Falgina</taxonomicName>
trib. n., described above.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
